FBIS3-19370 "drweu051_p_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-051 Document Type:Daily Report 16 Mar 1994 GREECE ELA Claims Responsibility for Bomb in Athens NC1603063994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 0500 GMT 16 Mar 94 NC1603063994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Text] The center of Athens was disturbed shortly after 0400 today when bombs planted at the European Union's Studies and Research Department and at the French Institute exploded. An unidentified caller telephoned before the explosions saying the bombs had been planted by the terrorist organization ELA [Revolutionary People's Struggle]. The explosions caused considerable damage.
